displayName: City of Canonas, the City of Laws

parameters:
Thief Nora: This is the city of Kanonas, governed by rules.
It's a city with a good atmosphere!

Mage Relm: Hehe, of course! We have a different history from
the barbaric Fotizona!

Clea: There might be children of pioneers here too. It would
be great if there were requests related to dragon
footprints.

Mage Relm: There are no such barbaric groups here. This city
is a city of philosophers, artists, and above all, mages!

Mage Relm: The center of this highly developed city is the
magic academy where genius me belongs!

Mage Relm: Hey, hold on, I'm still in the middle of
explaining!

Clea: If there is no information about dragons, let's finish
quickly.

Mage Relm: Grr... This is why ordinary people are so
frustrating.

Young artist: 'I'm glad I came out of Oros! In this town,
there should be people who will recognize me!'

Young artist: 'I'm glad I came out of Oros! In this town,
there should be people who will recognize me!'

Traveling peddler: 'Kanonas is a beautiful town, but
personally, I prefer Oros.'

Traveling peddler: 'Kanonas is a beautiful town, but
personally, I prefer Oros.'

Male Gardener: Aren't these plants beautiful? Being able to
skillfully manipulate scissors is my own kind of magic.

Female Mage: It's good to leave the room once in a while.
Being in the same room all the time makes your thoughts
stagnant, you know.

Female Mage: It's good to leave the room once in a while.
Being in the same room all the time makes your thoughts
stagnant, you know.
Traveling Bard: 'This is a really nice place, I like it.'
Traveling Bard: 'This is a really nice place, I like it.'
Do you want to enter the information broker?
Clea (Let's prepare first and then decide)
Clea: It seems like there's no mistake here.

Priestess Sophia: Hehe, if we negotiate honestly, it should
be fine.

Maid Niihi: What should we do... If this continues... I
might get fired from the mansion...
Maid Niihi: Could it be about the necklace...?
Clea: Could you please tell me the details?
Maid Niihi: Ah, I'm glad! Thank you, Goddess Imiserinos!
Mage Relm: So where should I go?
Maid Niihi: Ah, I'm sorry! I tend to be a bit clumsy...

Maid Niihi: It seems that I have dropped the pearl necklace
that I purchased at Ammos...

Maid Niihi: Please let me know when you're ready. I will
guide you through the route we have taken!
Maid Niihi: May I guide you?

Maid Niihi: The direction to Ammos is a desert road, so
please make sure to prepare properly!
Maid Niihi: May I guide you?
Mage Relm: Now, it's the promised pearl necklace.

Maid Niihi: What a surprise! You all are truly our saviors,
we've been saved...
Clea: Was it such an important thing?

Maid Niihi: The pearl necklace is Queen Caron's favorite,
and it's a big trend among the nobles, my lords.

Mage Relm: I don't really see much value in it, but I can't
quite understand the irrational thinking of the wealthy.

Maid Niihi: This is a promised gift and a personal thank
you!
Clea: Thank you for this expensive gift.
Maid Niihi: I pray for everyone's safe journey.

Maid Niihi: Everyone, you are our saviors! We pray to the
goddess Imiserinos for your safety.

Magic Academy Researcher: Um... The shopping I was asked to
do... I hope it gets approved soon so I can focus on my own
research.

Magic Academy Researcher: Oh, you're a young lady...!? The
crescent necklace... I apologize, are you from the academy?

Magic Academy Researcher: Um... The shopping I was asked to
do... I hope I can finish it quickly so I can focus on my
own research.
Kanonas Guard: The Magic Academy is ahead.

Kanonas Guardsman: Miss, my apologies... Are you from the
Academy?

Kanonas Guard: The Magic Academy is the largest magical
research institution in the empire.
Kanonas Guardsman: Good work on your research outside.
Mage Relm: It's more humid than I thought.
Mage Relm: And it's a very quiet night with no one around...

Mage Relm: It might be a reasonable action to take off a
little bit of clothing if it helps to cool down...
Mage Relm (...If I were to take off my clothes here)
Are you going to take off your clothes?

Mage Relm (If it's just a little bit... it should be okay,
right?)
Do you want to skip the adult scene?
Mage Relm: Haa... Haa... I'm glad... I wasn't found...

Mage Relm: I might be more tired than I imagined from doing
such foolish things.

Mage Relm: Haah... I'm tired from focusing too much on
foolish tasks.

Mage Relm: I'll take a little nap to get rid of my
fatigue...

Mage Relm: That's right! I should negate it! If I combine
the methods written in that book...
Mage Relm: I really am a genius, aren't I!
Mage Relm: The night breeze cools my head...

Mage Relm: A quiet night... It feels like I'm the only one
in the world...

Mage Relm: A world where it's just me... No one is here, no
one is here, a free space, a free time.

Mage Relm: This isn't an abnormal behavior, it's just the
stress making me feel strange...
Mage Relm: So it can't be helped, right...?
Would you like to skip the adult scene?
Mage Relm: I-I've done something terrible...

Mage Relm: I-I need to calm down and cool my head... Cool it
down...?

Mage Relm: That's right, I should cool it down! Heat the
stem and cool the leaves!
Mage Relm: I need to quickly make a prototype and bring it!

Mage Relm: It's a disaster to have to teach a student as
brilliant as this!

Mage Relm: Even Caron-kun can feel the overwhelming
difference in the quality of the teachers!

Mage Relm: You're not going to retort? There's no need to
worry about what happened back then, you know.
Mage Relm: ...What are you talking about?
Mage Anat: That child doesn't have any talent for magic.

Mage Anat: Anat and you should have been able to instantly
[understand] the magic circle itself.

Mage Anat: This is not something to learn, but a complete
talent. Unfortunately, that child will never reach it in
their lifetime.

Mage Anat: I've been sent by my father a few times for
social studies... It's really tough.

Mage Anat: It's seeing them chase after an impossible dream
with such determination.

Mage Relm: That may be true, but everyone should have the
right to chase their dreams!

Mage Anat: Since today is the last day of being a private
tutor, I intend to tell Caron to give up.
Mage Anat: It may be cruel, but... Anat will go.
Mage Anat: Thank you for saving me back then.
Mage Relm: Have you seen Mr. Furimata's son?

Deliveryman: If you're talking about Kalti-kun, I took him
all the way to the bakery.
Clea: Why would someone like Valie...

Deliveryman: I gave him a ride on my delivery. Apparently,
he needed to go to Valie for some magic studies or
something.

Mage Relm: Valie... growth... that conversation from back
then...

Deliveryman: Could it be that he ran away from home? If
that's the case, he's done something bad...
Mage Relm: That's right... the subjugation of the dragon...!

Mage Relm: It's Mount Monimos! Kalti-kun must have headed
towards Mount Monimos for sure!

Deliveryman: Haha, it's not a place where a child can go
alone.

Clea: Thank you for providing us with information, Relm-
san. I trust you.

Deliveryman: He's gone... I hope Kalti-kun comes back
safely.
Young Carti: I will definitely become a researcher!

Young Carti: And I will become Lady Relm's assistant! So
please wait for me, I will catch up soon!

Mage Relm: I am the prodigy of the Magic Academy. It's
impossible to catch up quickly without putting in a
significant amount of effort, you know?

Young Carti: Even so...! I will definitely stand by Lady
Relm's side!

Mage Relm: Hehehe, alright. I'll keep the assistant seat
open until you arrive.
Mage Relm: I'll be waiting, you know?
Mage Relm: Why is the Archmage here!?
Archmage: Hehe, shall we have a little chat?

Archmage: Academy mages should go outside once in a while.
There are too many shut-ins among us.

Mage Relm: Did you come here to oppose me fighting with Clea
and the others?

Archmage: As long as that man doesn't say anything, I have
no intention of restricting the actions of the Academy
personnel.

Archmage: Of course, if you lose, you plan to blame it on
Mage Relm acting on her own, right?
Mage Relm: You really have a good personality...!

Archmage: Are you aiming to become an Archmage? That means
you will do whatever it takes to protect the Magic Academy,
right?

Archmage: Do you have something you prioritize protecting
more than the Academy right now?

Mage Relm: I don't like Caron's ruthlessness, but to be
honest, I'm not interested in power struggles.

Mage Relm: I have decided to fight against Queen Caron
because there is something I want to protect, my precious
people.

Archmage: Hoho, you lack cunning. With that, you won't be
able to handle being a regular Archmage.

Archmage: Well, having an Archmage like that might not be a
bad thing.

Archmage: You have made many impossibilities possible in the
past, and this time, I expect you all to make the impossible
possible once again.

Archmage: I have the same dream as you... I hope we can
return to the Magic Academy together, as comrades who have
never given up.

Researcher Dokusa: Huff... huff... Hey, Relm-kun, isn't it a
bit fishy here?
Mage Relm: W-What's wrong? Why are you in such a hurry...!?

Researcher Dokusa: This is a gift for you, who fights
against the world's conspiracies!

\CL Relm has learned \C[14]Development Formula: Moon
Laurel\C[0]! \|
Mage Relm: T-Thank you very much...

Researcher Dokusa: I don't know what you're planning, and
perhaps neither you nor the Archmage have any intention of
speaking.

Researcher Dokusa: It's unavoidable, but I think the
deadline for our promise with you has come.

Researcher Dokusa: It's about book management! If you don't
come back, the important books will be ruined!
Mage Relm: Hehe, that's quite troublesome, isn't it?

Researcher Dokusa: So please make sure to come back. Until
then, I will take care of your treasures!

Mage Relm: Of course, even without being told! I am a genius
destined to become an Archmage!
